&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;KONUX is a dynamic and fast-growing technology company that is transforming the way the industry works. Our AI-powered solutions empower our customers to make smarter, data-driven decisions, and our culture is fueled by grit, ingenuity, and credibility - we believe that these values are essential to unlocking the potential of technology and making a real impact. At KONUX, we are passionate about driving innovation in the fields of IoT and AI, and we are looking for like-minded individuals to join our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Description:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an Engineering Manager to join our Data and Cloud Platform team. This team plays a central enabling role at KONUX: it provides the data and cloud foundations used by our product engineering teams, while also supporting Revenue, Operations, and other business functions in accessing, analysing, and acting on data.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will lead and grow a high-performing cross-functional team owning a broad platform scope, including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Data processing frameworks and scalable data platform capabilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cloud infrastructure, cost management, and observability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Platform security concepts, tenant configuration, and device management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Process automation, CI/CD pipelines, and developer enablement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will set clear priorities, align technical strategy with company goals, and help the team make sound trade-offs across reliability, scalability, security, data quality, cost, and delivery speed. You will combine strong people leadership with hands-on technical judgement: you should be able to assess technical designs, understand implementation risks, guide engineers towards pragmatic solutions, and contribute directly to the codebase or technical delivery where needed. You will also act as an important communication bridge between Engineering, Product, Revenue, Operations, and leadership, ensuring complex technical topics are clearly understood by both technical and non-technical stakeholders.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Impact&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Team Leadership&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effectively lead your cross-functional team consisting of 8 Fullstack, DevOps, and Data Engineers, as well as Technical Service Engineers, fostering collaboration, growth and development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct regular 1:1 meetings to provide coaching and support individual career development&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage performance reviews and pay adjustments according to the company framework&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support hiring, onboarding, feedback, conflict resolution, and performance management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Technical Delivery&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the architecture and technical strategy for the Data and Cloud Platform and collaborate with key stakeholders to align with the product roadmap and the needs of Revenue and Operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate company and technical goals into actionable plans for your team and ensure clear priorities and focus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Treat the platform as a product: understand internal users, prioritise high-leverage improvements, and balance reliability, scalability, security, cost, and delivery speed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute directly to technical delivery where needed, leading by example on data and software engineering, cloud infrastructure, and automation of operational processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assess technical designs hands-on, identify risks and trade-offs, and guide engineers towards pragmatic, maintainable solutions&lt;/li&gt;
